description: As comforting as a classic shepherd s pie - but starring our wild British park venison, rather than lamb - this warming dish is perfect for chilly nights.A creamy potato and parsnip topping is grilled until golden.
name: Venison stalker pie

description: Our healthy, Mexican-inspired spin on jacket potatoes.Oven-roasted sweet potato halves are smothered with a combo of simmered black beans, sweetcorn and baby plum tomatoes, then topped with a creamy, limey guacamole.
name: Mexican bean stuffed sweet potato with guacamole

description: Roasted until gooey, aubergine is an ideal partner for our pan-fried, pasture-grazed lamb, fragranced with garlic, cinnamon, smoked paprika and cumin.We drizzle over a cooling yoghurt sauce and sprinkle with juicy pomegranate seeds.
name: Middle Eastern aubergine, lamb and pomegranate

description: An easy traybake full of flavour.We coat free-range British chicken breasts in fragrant basil pesto, then roast over onion-sweetened tomato sauce with broccoli and pumpkin seeds.Chunks of butternut squash add vitamin A.
name: Pesto chicken with butternut and tomato bake

description: Fragrant thyme, sweet sundried tomato, earthy mushroom - our plant-based bolognese stars classic Italian flavours, but uses mineral-rich lentils rather than beef.We replace pasta with lighter courgetti, too, and sneak in crunch with pine nuts.This recipe has been approved by British Heart Foundation dietitians, helping to support heart and circulatory health.
name: Rich lentil bolognese with courgetti

description: We ve paired a succulent seared steak with a medley of spring vegetables including sweet baby carrots, crisp sugar snap peas and bright red radishes.
name: Seared beef with spring vegetable medley

description: Juicy, sustainably sourced cod, smothered in red curry paste - these skewers, griddled until golden, will transport you to the tropics.We pair them with potato salad, lifted with ginger and onion, and smoky pak choi.
name: Thai red fish skewers and grilled pak choi

description: Sockeye salmon with honey and mustard quinoa salad
name: Sockeye salmon with honey and mustard quinoa salad

description: This Spanish chicken dish is packed full of delicious Mediterranean flavours, perfect for a healthy, mid week meal.
name: Spanish chicken bake and griddled courgette

description: Family Favourite.Even the pickiest little eaters love burgers - especially when they re made from our grass-fed British beef and paired with fries and salad.We serve  em as you should, with sliced tomatoes and pickled onions.
name: Classic beef burger with sweet potato fries

description: Our sustainably caught cod is coated in Middle Eastern spice blend za atar, and lightly fried, alongside a pomegranate studded quinoa tabbouleh.
name: Za atar cod, pomegranate tabbouleh and harissa dip

description: Sustainably sourced salmon, topped with a herby almond crust - just the thing for a light and healthy dinner.We serve with potatoes coated in wholegrain mustard, and moreish sauerkraut made with crunchy caraway seeds and folate-rich beetroot.
name: Salmon, beet sauerkraut and mustard potatoes

description: Free-range British turkey coated in velvety coconut yoghurt and fragrant red pesto is served over a filling bed of brown rice, studded with vitamin K-source spinach.An easy and comforting midweek meal.
name: Creamy turkey and sundried tomato pesto casserole

description: Our sustainably sourced cod is so deliciously flaky, it doesn t need dressing up - here we bake it simply with just lemon, salt and pepper.It s paired with paprika-spiced butter beans, stewed with passata, and vitamin-rich Tenderstem broccoli.
name: Cod with spicy butter beans and lemon yoghurt

description: Our version of feijoada - Brazil s national dish - stews fibre-packing black beans with sweet pepper, earthy spices and rich raw cacao.We drizzle with creamed coconut, then spoon over brown rice.
name: Brazilian black bean stew and brown rice

description: Louisiana-spiced, grass-fed British beef burgers, topped with fried eggs - so delicious they don t even need buns.We pair them with mixed salad, herby dip and crisp carrot chips, sprinkled with addictive cashew  parmesan .
name: Southern bun-less burger and cheezy carrot chips

description: British free-range chicken thighs are smothered in garlic, harissa and chilli, then baked until juicy.You ll love them served over gooey spiced aubergine, and paired with pesto potatoes, fresh cucumber and coriander.
name: Harissa roasted aubergine with garlic and chilli chicken

description: It s our easy, healthy take on risotto - with brown rice, sweet sundried tomatoes and fragrant Italian herbs.We pack in greens with courgette and spinach, then top with a flaky baked fillet of sustainably sourced cod.
name: Cod with Italian-style tomato risotto
